data.description: The house is also rent to own. this gem of a townhouse at 3024 McDonald Street is located in the gated community of Enclave Grove within the desirable Coconut Grove neighborhood of Miami. The 2-story residence was built in 2006 and features 3 bedrooms, 2.5 bathrooms, and 2,318 square feet of living space. Marble and tile floors span throughout the home, and the kitchen includes recessed lighting and a breakfast bar. The master bedroom boasts beautiful dark hardwood floors and opens to a spacious balcony overlooking the manicured, tree-lined street. Unwind from a day at the beach in the master bathroom's large soaking tub. Outside, the stone tile patio in back is perfect for alfresco entertaining. Attached 2-car garage. Located close to many restaurants and shops, and approximately 1 mile from Dinner Key. Just 4 miles from the heart of the city.
